              <span slot="content">Stop Making Sense was a really great concert film with plenty of great energy, music, and photography to go around. Why I think this film stands out so much among concert films is because it&#39;s not just a camera shooting the stage. The cinematography is beautifully done, and it really makes you feel like you&#39;re not in the crowd but up there on the stage with the band and all their craziness. And much of the credit should go to the band themselves. It&#39;s probably no surprise, since I&#39;m watching this film, that I&#39;m a huge Talking Heads fan, so of course I absolutely loved the music in this film. The staging of this concert by the band is definitely a strong point in how they kept bringing out new members and doing new things. And then of course the band&#39;s energy and how excited many of them seemed also added to it. As far as concert films go, Stop Making Sense is pretty much as good as you can get.</span>
